tldr: The user wanted to add a database for questionnaire responses, a CSV
  export, and a simple admin dashboard with password-based authentication to
  their sleep questionnaire application. The plan was created and fully
  implemented, covering schema updates, API routes, authentication, and the
  dashboard UI.
overview: "The user aimed to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by
  integrating a database for storing responses, enabling CSV data export, and
  providing a straightforward admin dashboard for data access. The project
  involved a comprehensive approach: updating the application's demographic data
  structure, defining a new  model within Prisma for
  database interaction, and developing a suite of API endpoints for data
  submission, retrieval, and CSV export. A key decision was to implement a
  simple password-based authentication system using environment variables and
  secure HTTP-only cookies to protect the admin dashboard. The dashboard itself
  was designed to be user-friendly, featuring a table view of responses,
  pagination, and a CSV download option. The entire implementation was
  completed, addressing all specified requirements and preparing the application
  for deployment with NeonDB. The user's final query suggests an interest in
  exploring even simpler authentication mechanisms."
